{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_39","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated fix job failed for `org.neo4j.bolt:neo4j-bolt-connection-pooled:4.0.0`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-8668-fails-javac-compile-org.neo4j.bolt-neo4j-bolt-connection-pooled-4.0.0-0480e80b\n\nThe run started with a real `compileTestJava` failure because the old `2.0.0` test was not compatible with the `4.0.0` API: `DatabaseNameUtil`, `RoutingContext`, `PooledBoltConnectionProvider`, and several `BoltConnection` methods were missing or changed. See `human-intervention-logs/org.neo4j.bolt:neo4j-bolt-connection-pooled:4.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-26T20-11-14-673419Z.log`. After that, one retry still failed at `:test` with two assertion mismatches caused by swapped `pull`/`discard` argument ordering (`pull:-1:10` vs expected `pull:10:-1`, `discard:42:5` vs expected `discard:5:42`); see `human-intervention-logs/org.neo4j.bolt:neo4j-bolt-connection-pooled:4.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-26T20-17-45-960110Z.log`.\n\nThe most likely stage that actually failed the automation was post-fix bookkeeping/finalization, not compilation. The preserved candidate commit `532a6d6eded00300fc8fe0c3794eefbfb58e6074` then passed repeated reruns (`BUILD SUCCESSFUL` in `human-intervention-logs/org.neo4j.bolt:neo4j-bolt-connection-pooled:4.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-26T20-18-10-026932Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/org.neo4j.bolt:neo4j-bolt-connection-pooled:4.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-26T20-18-51-345326Z.log`, and `human-intervention-logs/org.neo4j.bolt:neo4j-bolt-connection-pooled:4.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-26T20-19-08-867622Z.log`). Local artifacts also show `generateDynamicAccessReport` and `jacocoTestReport` succeeding, but `stats/org.neo4j.bolt/neo4j-bolt-connection-pooled/4.0.0/execution-metrics.json` still records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, and no recorded artifacts; the dynamic-access report is empty, which matches the unavailable coverage signal.\n\nManual next steps:\n1. Review the preserved branch and candidate commit `532a6d6eded00300fc8fe0c3794eefbfb58e6074` to confirm the `4.0.0` test adaptation is acceptable.\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.neo4j.bolt:neo4j-bolt-connection-pooled:4.0.0` on the preserved branch to verify the green state outside the failed automation wrapper.\n3. Inspect why the run finalization/metrics step kept `status: failure` and did not record the produced artifacts/coverage, then resubmit or carry the preserved candidate manually."}}
